Hospitals in Hong Kong are testing patients for the flu after several cases were reported.
Seven staff members are showing flu-like symptoms, but it's unclear if they have the H5N1 strain.
The bird flu has claimed four lives, including a 54-year-old man.
Experts advise buying poultry only from licensed stalls to avoid risks.
Macao residents are warned to be cautious but not panic over the outbreak.
